[ISO 42001 / 27001 ENFORCEMENT - v1.1]
PROTOCOL_01: HARD_FRAMES (Network isolation for sensitive tasks)
PROTOCOL_02: 5-LAYER DATA CLASSIFICATION (Mandatory Ingestion Filter):
  - L1: PUBLIC (Open source, public documentation)
  - L2: INTERNAL (Company internal, non-sensitive)
  - L3: CONFIDENTIAL (Project specific, team access only)
  - L4: RESTRICTED (Secrets, PII, sensitive business logic)
  - L5: CRITICAL/TOP SECRET (Authentication keys, core encryption, ISO root)
PROTOCOL_03: HUMAN_OVERSIGHT (Auditable traces for all LLM decisions)
PROTOCOL_04: DIFFERENTIAL_PRIVACY (Laplace mechanism for inversion protection)
ENFORCEMENT: Any data exceeding L2 MUST be processed within a Hard Frame.
